section.section:
Of the 11 members of the Board:
One shall be a member of the Maryland House of Delegates appointed by the Speaker of the House;
One shall be a member of the Senate of Maryland appointed by the President of the Senate;
Four shall be individuals with knowledge and expertise concerning spinal cord injuries appointed by the Governor from separate lists submitted to the Governor by the University of Maryland School of Medicine and the Johns Hopkins School of Medicine, with:
Two individuals from the University of Maryland School of Medicine; and
Two individuals from the Johns Hopkins School of Medicine;
Two shall be nurses with knowledge and expertise concerning spinal cord injuries appointed by the Governor from separate lists submitted to the Governor by the University of Maryland School of Nursing and the Johns Hopkins School of Nursing, with:
One nurse from the University of Maryland School of Nursing; and
One nurse from the Johns Hopkins School of Nursing;
Two members, appointed by the Governor from a list submitted by the Department of Disabilities, shall be individuals who have a spinal cord injury or who have a family member with a spinal cord injury; and
One member, appointed by the Governor, shall be an individual from the general public with knowledge and expertise concerning spinal cord injuries.
